&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A day in the life&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Reliability Engineer at Swift, you will work on module reliability and IEC testing and dive deep into identifying and understanding failure mechanisms on the module level. You will interact frequently and work closely with both module and cell R&amp;amp;D, supporting the development of a stable and reliable product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a typical day, you might field modules at our local outdoor test site, experiment with accelerated testing conditions to reproduce module field failures, and create a test plan for external analytical labs to investigate module failures. You may meet with team members from the R&amp;amp;D team to understand current developments on the cell and module level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an early hire, you’ll help craft Swift’s culture. In this role you’ll be interacting with every part of the company, which will naturally lead to many opportunities to grow your own skills and responsibilities. We encourage you to take full advantage of these opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
